1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,560
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:03,560 --> 00:00:04,560
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:04,560 --> 00:00:09,640
My name is Catherine and today we're talking about something that is, well, not so fun
我是Catherine，今天我们聊的话题，嗯，可不太愉快。

4
00:00:09,640 --> 00:00:10,640
when it happens.
当它发生的时候。

5
00:00:10,640 --> 00:00:11,640
That's right.
没错。

6
00:00:11,640 --> 00:00:16,680
Today we're going to talk about those situations where people are trying to take advantage
今天我们要聊聊那些别人想占我们便宜的情况。

7
00:00:16,680 --> 00:00:17,680
of us.
占我们便宜。

8
00:00:17,680 --> 00:00:18,680
All right.
好的。

9
00:00:18,680 --> 00:00:20,720
They're lying to us so they can take our money.
他们对我们撒谎，好骗走我们的钱。

10
00:00:20,720 --> 00:00:23,940
Let's take a listen to today's dialogue and when we come back in a moment, we'll be talking
我们来听听今天的对话，稍后回来时，我们会聊聊你即将听到的一些单词和短语。

11
00:00:23,940 --> 00:00:32,320
about some of these words and phrases that you're about to hear.
我们来听听今天的对话，稍后回来时，我们会聊聊你即将听到的一些单词和短语。

12
00:00:32,320 --> 00:00:34,040
I got an urgent email from Tom.
我收到汤姆发来的一封紧急邮件。

13
00:00:34,040 --> 00:00:38,000
He says he's in London and got robbed and needs us to wire him some money for his hotel.
他说他在伦敦被抢了，需要我们给他电汇一些钱付酒店费用。

14
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:39,000
What?
什么？

15
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:40,960
That sounds really dodgy to me.
我觉得这听起来很可疑。

16
00:00:40,960 --> 00:00:41,960
No way.
不可能。

17
00:00:41,960 --> 00:00:42,960
Tom is an honest person.
汤姆是个诚实的人。

18
00:00:42,960 --> 00:00:43,960
He wouldn't lie to me.
他不会对我撒谎。

19
00:00:43,960 --> 00:00:48,360
No, I mean, it seems like someone may have hacked his email account and sent that out.
不，我是说，好像有人黑了他的邮箱账户，发了那封邮件。

20
00:00:48,360 --> 00:00:49,640
I mean, think about it.
我是说，你想想看。

21
00:00:49,640 --> 00:00:51,720
Why would he email you instead of calling you?
他为什么不打电话给你，而要发邮件呢？

22
00:00:51,720 --> 00:00:55,160
Do you really think someone is trying to scam people into sending money?
你真的觉得有人想骗人寄钱吗？

23
00:00:55,160 --> 00:00:56,160
For sure.
当然。

24
00:00:56,160 --> 00:00:57,600
There's so many con artists out there.
外面骗子太多了。

25
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:59,080
You never really know.
你永远搞不清楚。

26
00:00:59,080 --> 00:01:01,920
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

27
00:01:01,920 --> 00:01:09,640
So let's take a look at some language on Language Takeaway.
那我们来“语言小贴士”环节看看一些语言点。

28
00:01:09,640 --> 00:01:14,240
In Language Takeaway, Marco, one of the first things we hear is that I got an urgent email
在“语言小贴士”里，Marco，我们听到的第一件事是“我收到汤姆发来的一封紧急邮件”。

29
00:01:14,240 --> 00:01:15,240
from Tom.
没错。

30
00:01:15,240 --> 00:01:16,240
That's right.
所以这是一个形容词，表示紧急的东西。

31
00:01:16,240 --> 00:01:18,820
So this is an adjective, something that is urgent.
它是紧急的。

32
00:01:18,820 --> 00:01:19,820
It's urgent.
意思是需要立刻处理。

33
00:01:19,820 --> 00:01:23,240
It means it needs to be looked at immediately.
非常重要。

34
00:01:23,240 --> 00:01:24,520
It's very important.
没错。

35
00:01:24,520 --> 00:01:25,520
That's right.
所以你可以有一封紧急邮件。

36
00:01:25,520 --> 00:01:28,080
So you can have an urgent email.
意思是一封非常重要的邮件，或者某种情况可能是紧急的。

37
00:01:28,080 --> 00:01:32,640
That means it's a very important email or something in a situation can be urgent.
对，就像紧急情况。

38
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:34,640
Yeah, like an emergency.
所以是紧急护理。

39
00:01:34,640 --> 00:01:36,280
So urgent care.
我们在医院里会说到。

40
00:01:36,280 --> 00:01:37,640
We talk about at the hospital.
就是需要医生立刻、紧急处理的事情。

41
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:41,960
It's something that needs to be looked at by a doctor immediately, urgently.
没错。

42
00:01:41,960 --> 00:01:42,960
That's right.
紧急地。

43
00:01:42,960 --> 00:01:43,960
Urgently.
那是副词形式。

44
00:01:43,960 --> 00:01:44,960
That would be the adverb.
然后我们接着说，这封邮件很紧急，因为是汤姆发来的，邮件里说他在伦敦被抢了。

45
00:01:44,960 --> 00:01:51,800
So we go on to say that the email is urgent because it's from Tom and the email said that
然后我们接着说，这封邮件很紧急，因为是汤姆发来的，邮件里说他在伦敦被抢了。

46
00:01:51,800 --> 00:01:54,360
he is in London and he got robbed.
好的，他被抢了。

47
00:01:54,360 --> 00:01:56,640
All right, he got robbed.
好的。

48
00:01:56,640 --> 00:01:57,640
All right.
所以“抢劫”是动词，R-O-B，但这里重要的是看动词“got”。

49
00:01:57,640 --> 00:02:04,200
So to rob is the verb, R-O-B, but here it's important to look at the verb got.
这意味着无论发生什么，都是发生在他身上，也就是这个朋友，被别人抢了。

50
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:09,960
This means that whatever's happening, it happened to him, to the friend by someone else.
没错。

51
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:10,960
That's right.
所以有人抢了他。

52
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:12,600
So someone robbed him.
好的，他被抢了。

53
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:14,600
All right, he got robbed.
意思是有人拿走了他的钱，对吧？

54
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:17,480
That means someone took his money, right?
没错。

55
00:02:17,480 --> 00:02:18,480
That's right.
所以动词是“get”，而“robbed”是形容词，以ed结尾，但我们也有动词“rob”，如果你抢劫某人，意思是你偷了他的钱。

56
00:02:18,480 --> 00:02:25,600
So the verb would be to get and robbed would be an adjective ending ed, but we also have
所以动词是“get”，而“robbed”是形容词，以ed结尾，但我们也有动词“rob”，如果你抢劫某人，意思是你偷了他的钱。

57
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:32,800
the verb to rob and if you rob someone, that means that you are stealing his or her money.
对，如果我抢了Marco，意思是我从他那里拿走了钱，但如果我被Marco抢了，意思是他拿走了我的钱。

58
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:39,640
Yeah, if I rob Marco, it means I take Marco's money from him, but if I got robbed by Marco,
对，如果我抢了Marco，意思是我从他那里拿走了钱，但如果我被Marco抢了，意思是他拿走了我的钱。

59
00:02:39,640 --> 00:02:41,920
it means he took my money.
没错。

60
00:02:41,920 --> 00:02:42,920
That's right.
所以如果你单独用动词“rob”，意思是你正在做这个动作，或者有人正在偷另一个人的东西，但如果你“get robbed”或一个人“got robbed”，意思是他或她的钱被拿走了。

61
00:02:42,920 --> 00:02:47,920
So if you use the verb to rob by itself, that means that you are doing the action or someone
所以如果你单独用动词“rob”，意思是你正在做这个动作，或者有人正在偷另一个人的东西，但如果你“get robbed”或一个人“got robbed”，意思是他或她的钱被拿走了。

62
00:02:47,920 --> 00:02:54,400
is stealing from another person, but if you get robbed or a person got robbed, that means
现在这个朋友被抢了，有人拿走了他的钱，我们被要求给他电汇一些钱。

63
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:57,800
he or her got money taken from him.
现在这个朋友被抢了，有人拿走了他的钱，我们被要求给他电汇一些钱。

64
00:02:57,800 --> 00:03:04,600
Now the friend got robbed, someone took his money and we've been asked to wire him some
好的，电汇钱。

65
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:05,600
money.
没错，电汇钱。

66
00:03:05,600 --> 00:03:07,200
Okay, to wire money.
这基本上就是寄钱的意思。

67
00:03:07,200 --> 00:03:08,840
That's right, to wire money.
这是一种非常古老的寄钱方式。

68
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:10,640
This basically means to send money.
基本上你是通过电子方式寄钱。

69
00:03:10,640 --> 00:03:14,760
It's a very old way or form of sending money.
你不是真的买个信封，放些钱进去，然后邮寄。

70
00:03:14,760 --> 00:03:16,960
Basically you're sending money electronically.
你去银行或西联汇款，通过电子方式转账。

71
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:21,440
You don't actually buy an envelope and put some money in it and send it in the mail.
没错。

72
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:26,560
You go to a bank or Western Union and you transfer the money electronically.
所以发送电子转账，我们通常说“wire someone some money”。

73
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:27,560
That's right.
对，我会电汇给你。

74
00:03:27,560 --> 00:03:33,120
So to send an electronic transfer of money, we usually say you wire someone some money.
没错。

75
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:35,160
Yeah, I'll wire it to you.
好的。

76
00:03:35,160 --> 00:03:36,160
That's right.
所以今天课程的主题是关于人们试图诈骗其他人。

77
00:03:36,160 --> 00:03:37,160
All right.
好的，这里的动词“scam”意思是撒谎或对某人不诚实，以便拿走他们的钱或占他们便宜。

78
00:03:37,160 --> 00:03:43,520
So the main topic about today's lesson is about people trying to scam other people.
所以今天课程的主题是关于人们试图诈骗其他人。

79
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:50,520
All right, here the verb to scam means to lie or to be dishonest with someone so that
好的，这里的动词“scam”意思是撒谎或对某人不诚实，以便拿走他们的钱或占他们便宜。

80
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:55,120
you can take their money or to take advantage of them.
好的，这里的动词“scam”意思是撒谎或对某人不诚实，以便拿走他们的钱或占他们便宜。

81
00:03:55,120 --> 00:03:56,120
That's right.
没错。

82
00:03:56,120 --> 00:04:01,960
So to scam means to take advantage of someone, to lie to someone, but you also have a scam,
所以，“scam”意思是利用某人、对某人撒谎，但“scam”也可以作名词，

83
00:04:01,960 --> 00:04:06,820
a noun, which is a situation where people are trying to take your money.
指一种试图骗走你钱的情况。

84
00:04:06,820 --> 00:04:12,800
So a very famous scam might be people in a big city like Paris saying, Oh, I'm a tourist.
一个很有名的骗局可能是，在巴黎这样的大城市里，有人说：“哦，我是个游客。”

85
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:13,800
I'm lost.
“我迷路了。”

86
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:14,800
Can you help me?
“你能帮我吗？”

87
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:17,600
Can you give me some money to go to the train station?
“你能给我点钱去火车站吗？”

88
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:19,720
And really these people, they're not lost.
实际上这些人并不迷路。

89
00:04:19,720 --> 00:04:21,640
They just want you to give them money.
他们只是想让你给他们钱。

90
00:04:21,640 --> 00:04:22,640
That's right.
没错。

91
00:04:22,640 --> 00:04:23,640
This is called a scam.
这就叫骗局。

92
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:27,960
And what they're doing is they are trying to scam you.
而他们正在做的就是试图骗你。

93
00:04:27,960 --> 00:04:29,240
That's right.
没错。

94
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:33,040
And so we actually have a word for these type of people.
所以我们确实有一个词来形容这类人。

95
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,760
We say they are con artists.
我们说他们是“骗子艺术家”。

96
00:04:34,760 --> 00:04:36,640
They are conning you.
他们在骗你。

97
00:04:36,640 --> 00:04:37,640
A con artist.
一个骗子艺术家。

98
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:38,640
Okay.
好的。

99
00:04:38,640 --> 00:04:39,840
So we know what an artist is.
所以我们知道什么是艺术家。

100
00:04:39,840 --> 00:04:46,400
An artist is a person who maybe paints pictures or makes something creative.
艺术家是可能画画或创作一些有创意东西的人。

101
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:49,800
But a con is someone who breaks the law.
但骗子就是违法的人。

102
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:54,200
So a con artist is someone who creatively breaks the law.
所以骗子艺术家就是创造性地违法的人。

103
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:55,200
That's right.
没错。

104
00:04:55,200 --> 00:05:01,300
So these are basically thieves or people who take advantage of other people or steal from
所以这些人基本上就是小偷，或者以非常有创意的方式利用他人、从他人那里偷东西的人。

105
00:05:01,300 --> 00:05:03,860
other people in a very creative way.
从他人那里偷东西的人。

106
00:05:03,860 --> 00:05:09,300
So there are situations where they may sell something that doesn't even really belong
所以有些情况下，他们可能会卖掉甚至不属于他们的东西。

107
00:05:09,300 --> 00:05:10,300
to them.
不属于他们的东西。

108
00:05:10,300 --> 00:05:11,300
That's right.
没错。

109
00:05:11,300 --> 00:05:16,480
So the thing to remember here with a con artist is that there's almost always a story.
所以这里要记住，骗子艺术家几乎总是会编一个故事。

110
00:05:16,480 --> 00:05:20,720
You know, you have to, they give you this story and they make you believe them and then
你知道，他们得给你讲这个故事，让你相信他们，然后

111
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:25,320
you give them money or you give them some help that they don't deserve and that way
你就给他们钱，或者给他们一些他们不配得到的帮助，这样

112
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:26,840
they take it away from you.
他们就从你这里拿走了。

113
00:05:26,840 --> 00:05:27,840
That's right.
没错。

114
00:05:27,840 --> 00:05:28,840
All right.
好了。

115
00:05:28,840 --> 00:05:29,980
So we've taken a look at a lot of language here.
我们这里看了很多语言点。

116
00:05:29,980 --> 00:05:38,240
Let's take a break, listen to the dialogue again and we'll be back in a bit.
我们休息一下，再听一遍对话，一会儿回来。

117
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:39,960
I got an urgent email from Tom.
我收到汤姆的一封紧急邮件。

118
00:05:39,960 --> 00:05:44,040
He says he's in London and got robbed and needs us to wire him some money for his hotel.
他说他在伦敦被抢了，需要我们给他汇点钱付酒店费。

119
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:45,040
What?
什么？

120
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:46,880
That sounds really dodgy to me.
我觉得这听起来很可疑。

121
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:47,880
No way.
不可能。

122
00:05:47,880 --> 00:05:48,880
Tom is an honest person.
汤姆是个诚实的人。

123
00:05:48,880 --> 00:05:49,880
He wouldn't lie to me.
他不会骗我的。

124
00:05:49,880 --> 00:05:54,280
No, I mean, it seems like someone may have hacked his email account and sent that out.
不，我是说，好像有人黑了他的邮箱，发了那封邮件。

125
00:05:54,280 --> 00:05:55,560
I mean, think about it.
你想想看。

126
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:57,640
Why would he email you instead of calling you?
他为什么不打电话给你，而要发邮件呢？

127
00:05:57,640 --> 00:06:01,080
Do you really think someone is trying to scam people into sending money?
你真的觉得有人想骗人寄钱吗？

128
00:06:01,080 --> 00:06:02,080
For sure.
当然。

129
00:06:02,080 --> 00:06:03,520
There's so many con artists out there.
外面骗子太多了。

130
00:06:03,520 --> 00:06:07,520
You never really know.
你永远搞不清楚。

131
00:06:07,520 --> 00:06:08,520
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

132
00:06:08,520 --> 00:06:14,240
Let's take a look at four key phrases on Fluency Builder.
我们来看看流利度训练中的四个关键短语。

133
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:17,440
Fluency Builder.
流利度训练。

134
00:06:17,440 --> 00:06:19,280
So we've got two friends who are talking.
我们有两个朋友在聊天。

135
00:06:19,280 --> 00:06:24,680
One friend says that they got an urgent email from Tom and the other says, wow, that sounds
一个朋友说他们收到了汤姆的一封紧急邮件，另一个说，哇，这听起来

136
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:26,840
really dodgy to me.
真的很可疑。

137
00:06:26,840 --> 00:06:27,840
Just right.
没错。

138
00:06:27,840 --> 00:06:33,840
So if something sounds dodgy or something is dodgy, it means it doesn't really sound
所以如果某事听起来可疑或某事可疑，意思是它听起来不太

139
00:06:33,840 --> 00:06:37,280
believable or correct or legal.
可信、正确或合法。

140
00:06:37,280 --> 00:06:38,280
That's right.
对。

141
00:06:38,280 --> 00:06:40,800
So maybe I can't trust it.
所以也许我不能信任它。

142
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:45,560
Something is dodgy if it doesn't sound like something I would want to trust.
如果某件事听起来不像我愿意信任的，那它就有问题。

143
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:48,320
And I think you can say it about a situation.
而且我觉得你可以用它来形容一个情况。

144
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:53,280
So this robbery, it sounds quite dodgy.
所以这起抢劫案听起来相当可疑。

145
00:06:53,280 --> 00:06:54,920
You can also say it about food, right?
你也可以用它来形容食物，对吧？

146
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:55,920
Right.
对。

147
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:58,600
So if something looks kind of dodgy, it means it doesn't really look safe.
所以如果某样东西看起来有点可疑，那就意味着它看起来不太安全。

148
00:06:58,600 --> 00:06:59,600
Yeah.
是的。

149
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:01,000
Maybe I'll be sick if I eat it.
也许我吃了会生病。

150
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:02,760
So it's quite dodgy looking.
所以它看起来相当可疑。

151
00:07:02,760 --> 00:07:03,760
Right.
对。

152
00:07:03,760 --> 00:07:04,760
Or even a person can look dodgy.
甚至一个人也可以看起来可疑。

153
00:07:04,760 --> 00:07:07,160
So maybe that person is not really someone you want to trust.
所以那个人可能不是你真正想信任的人。

154
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:09,800
A con artist doesn't always look dodgy.
骗子并不总是看起来可疑。

155
